---
title: Thyme Gravy Pork Chops with Asparagus and Mashed Potatoes
description: Although we love exploring new cuisines and flavors, not every night of the week has to be an adventure. Sometimes, you just wanna kick back with the classics. This recipe was made for just that. Mashed potatoes, pork chops, and roasted asparagus with an herby gravy mean no funny business here. Just pure deliciousness that everyone in your family will love.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5a53abe22c9e86757b651682-1c1ebf8b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/thyme-gravy-pork-chops-5a53abe22c9e86757b651682-9f8208cc.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
time required: 45 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 43 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 340 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/thyme-gravy-pork-chops-5a53abe22c9e86757b651682
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Place in a
#medium pot{} with a pinch of @salt{} and enough water to cover by 1 inch.
Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, about
~{12%minutes}. Drain, then return to pot.

Trim woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{16%ounce}. Mince @Chives{¼%ounce}.
Cut @Lemon{1} into wedges. Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon}
in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @Pork Chops{24%ounce} dry with a
#paper towel{}. Season with @salt{}, @Pepper{}, and 1 TSBP
@Flour{2%tablespoon} (we sent more). Cook in pan until just browned, about
~{2%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #baking sheet{}, placing toward one side.

Toss asparagus with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{} on empty side of sheet
with pork. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Bake in oven until asparagus
starts to brown and pork reaches desired doneness, ~{7-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If pork is done before asparagus, remove from sheet and let asparagus
> finish.

Let pork rest on a #plate{} for ~{5%minutes} after it's done.

Pour out any grease in pan used for pork. Add @Butter{2%tablespoon} and
remaining flour to same pan over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until butter is
melted and a pasty mixture has formed, ~{1-2%minutes}. Whisk in
@Chicken Demi-Glace{1}, @Thyme{¼%ounce} sprigs, and ⅔ cup water until smooth.
Simmer until thickened, about ~{2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.
Remove pan from heat. Stir in a squeeze of lemon.

Add @Milk{½%cup} and chives to pot with drained potatoes (add the chives to
taste—you may not use all). Mash with #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth.
Season generously with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> TIP: Add more milk if needed to give potatoes a creamy consistency.

Stir any juices released by pork into gravy in pan. Divide potatoes, pork,
and asparagus between #plates{}. Remove and discard thyme sprigs from gravy,
then spoon gravy over everything. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the
side for squeezing over.